    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-05-28T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-05-28T06:00:00-05:00" n="441"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d441">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">320.2 AA/5–2852: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 441<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Lebanon (<persName corresp="#p_MHB1"
                            type="from">Minor</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d441fn1">Identified also as telegram <gloss
                            target="#t_Rapun1">Rapun</gloss> 289. Repeated to Tel Aviv.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Beirut</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-05-28T13:00:00+02:00"
                            >May 28, 1952—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1323. <persName corresp="#p_BJB1">Blandford</persName> saw <persName
                        corresp="#p_BGD1">Ben-Gurion</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_EW1"
                        >Eytan</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_CM1">Comay</persName> Jerusalem
                    26th. Israelis apparently stated they now accept principle of taking full
                    responsibility refugees. When pressed by <persName corresp="#p_BJB1"
                        >Blandford</persName> for definite date they tentatively suggested Sept 1.
                        <persName corresp="#p_BJB1">Blandford</persName> pushed for July 1. Israelis
                    promised consult the several Ministries concerned with problem and inform agency
                    their position next ten days.</p>
                <p>2. <persName corresp="#p_BGD1">Ben-Gurion</persName> displayed surprising lack
                    info refugee problem expressing such mistaken beliefs as (a) all refugees in
                    first class camps and living well; (b) problem solving itself as refugees being
                    absorbed into economies of countries of refuge. <persName corresp="#p_BJB1"
                        >Blandford</persName> pointed out we have 100,000 more refugees than when we
                    started, only one-third living in camps, and at least half million must be moved
                    to other countries before resettlement.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MHB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Minor</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
